  "generated_text": "To determine how many years it takes to start earning money, we need to compare the total cost of planting the tree against the total revenue from selling the lemons.\n\n**1. Identify the costs and revenues:**\n*   **Planting Cost:** $\\$90$ (One-time cost).\n*   **Annual Water/Feed Cost:** $\\$3$ per year.\n*   **Lemon Yield per year:** $7$ lemons.\n*   **Selling Price per lemon:** $\\$1.50$.\n\n**2. Calculate the profit per year (excluding the initial planting cost):**\nFirst, find the total revenue generated in one year:\n$$ \\text{Annual Revenue} = 7 \\text{ lemons} \\times \\$1.50/\\text{lemon} = \\$10.50 $$\n\nNext, find the total annual operating cost:\n$$ \\text{Annual Cost} = \\$3.00 $$\n\nNow, calculate the net profit (revenue minus operating costs) for each year:\n$$ \\text{Net Profit} = \\$10.50 - \\$3.00 = \\$7.50 $$\n\n**3. Determine when the total cost is recovered:**\nCarlos needs to recover the initial planting cost of $\\$90$. We divide the planting cost by the annual profit to find the number of years required to break even:\n$$ \\text{Years to break even} = \\frac{\\text{Planting Cost}}{\\text{Annual Profit}} $$\n$$ \\text{Years to break even} = \\frac{90}{7.50} $$\n\nPerform the division:\n$$ 90 \\div 7.5 = \\frac{900}{75} = 12 $$\n\n**4. Conclusion:**\n",
